content:
Select the subject, description, and additional Case fields for Einstein to ground on. Einstein uses details from your selected case fields to draft personalized responses.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions with the Einstein for Service add-on.

In Service AI Grounding Setup, under the Case tab, select Edit.
Under Required Fields, select Subject Field and Description Field. Choose default subject and description fields or use custom fields.
Case comments and emails are included for grounding by default.

For example, you can replace the default subject field with a custom field labeled Contact Reason.
Click Save.
Activate grounding for your Case records.

Einstein begins indexing your cases. Indexing can take several hours depending on the number of cases you have in Salesforce.

To consider case comments or emails when you ground for Knowledge Creation, go to Additional Object Grounding Options and select Include Case Emails and Include Case Comments.

Field level security limits the grounded responses that users can see.
Encrypted fields aren’t supported for grounding. Einstein can’t ground on or make predictions for encrypted fields.
Service AI Grounding only supports String and Text Area type fields.
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Grounding with Cases
